    "summary": "With a solid grounding in international contemporary visual arts, I am employed as senior project officer international relations for the Mondriaan Fund in The Netherlands. At the Fund I\u2019m responsible for introducing international art professionals to contemporary art in the Netherlands, and the organization of the annual Orientation Trips. Before starting at the Mondriaan Fund I worked as a freelancer with different national and international commissioners in the fields of the visual arts.\n \nI studied Hotel Management, Heerlen (1980-1984) and Art Management at the Amsterdamse Hogeschool voor de Kunsten (1988-1992).",
