                    "company": "Mondriaan Fund",
                    "description": "I am responsible for the development and management of both the visitors\u2019 program and the orientation trips and contribute to the development of the general  international policy of the Mondriaan Fund. \n\nWith The International Visitors\u2019 Program the Mondriaan Fund aims to increase the international appreciation of contemporary art from the Netherlands, to expand the international networks of art professionals in the Netherlands and to further the international position of artists based in the Netherlands. Significant international curators are offered a program developed and tailored to their field of interest. The selection of guests is based on upcoming biennials, festivals or major contemporary art events. In the past 10 years I have received more than 450 guests, resulting in a strong Dutch presence at many significant international art platforms like biennials in  Sydney, Berlin, Gwangju and Kochi.\n\nNext to the visitors program I am responsible for the Orientation Trip, to relevant contemporary art platforms in the world. The purpose of these trips is to expand the international networks of art professionals from the Netherlands, Belgium, Denmark and Switzerland. \n\nTrips have led to:\nIran and Armenia (2016) | Chile and Colombia (2015) | Korea and Japan (2014) | Estonia, Lithuania, Poland, Slovakia and Hungary (2013) | Indonesia and China (2012) | Mali, Senegal and Morocco (2011) | Turkey, Nigeria and Mali (2010) | Brazil, Argentina and Peru (2009) | Bangladesh, India and the United Arab Emirates (2008) | Mexico and Cura\u00e7ao (2007) and South Africa and Senegal (2006).\n\nIn addition to this I am  member of the organization team involved with the Dutch entry at the Venice Biennale. I coordinated the project \"Focus The Netherlands\" at the art fair Arco Madrid (2012) and in Moscow \u201cThe Dutch Art Assembly\u201d during the celebration of 400 years bilateral relation between The Netherlands and Russia (2013).",
                    "title": "International Visitors Program",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
